# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;           // 2π (full circle in radians)
var PHI = 1.618;           // Golden ratio
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;     // √(1/2)

// Physics/simulation configuration
var config = {
    repulsion: 4000,       // Node repulsion strength
    compliance: 0.004,     // Spring compliance
    refractory: 0.92,      // Velocity damping factor
    diffusion: 0.0003,     // Center-pull strength
    saturation: 40,        // Max number of particles
    resistance: 0.04,      // Particle drag
    diastolic: 0.06        // Camera/viewport easing speed
};

// ===== NODES (vertices in a graph) =====
var nodes = [
    { id: "hub",     label: "Hub",     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",   label: "Alpha",   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",    label: "Beta",    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",   label: "Gamma",   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",   label: "Delta",   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon", label: "Epsilon", r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// ===== EDGES (springs connecting nodes) =====
var edges = [
    { a: "hub",   b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "hub",   b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma", b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha", b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// ===== CAMERA STATE =====
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// ===== PARTICLES =====
var particles = [];
var tick = 0;

// Find a node by ID
function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// ===== PHYSICS SIMULATION STEP =====
function simulate() {
    // 1. Node-to-node REPULSION (Coulomb's law style)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. SPRING FORCES along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || config.compliance) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. CENTER GRAVITY + DAMPING + position update
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * config.diffusion;  // pull toward center x=400
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * config.diffusion;  // pull toward center y=300
        nodes[n].vx *= config.refractory;  // damping
        nodes[n].vy *= config.refractory;
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

// ===== SPAWN PARTICLES =====
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.saturation) return;  // max 40 particles

    var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

// ===== UPDATE PARTICLES =====
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;  // drag
        p.vy *= 1 - config.resistance * 0.125;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);  // remove expired
    }
}

// ===== SMOOTH CAMERA =====
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.diastolic;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.diastolic;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.diastolic;
}

// ===== MAIN LOOP =====
function update() {
    simulate();
    updateParticles();
    if (tick % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();  // spawn every 3rd frame
    updateCamera();
    tick++;
}

setInterval(update, 16);  // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation engine** — the physics backend for a network visualization. Specifically:

### 🔵 Graph Layout (Force-Directed)
- **6 nodes** ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") connected by **8 spring edges**
- Nodes **repel** each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges)
- Edges act as **springs** (Hooke's law) pulling connected nodes toward a rest length
- A gentle **gravity** pulls everything toward center (400, 300)
- **Velocity damping** (0.92) prevents infinite oscillation

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a particle spawns from a random node
- Particles drift outward with drag, and die after 800–2000 frames
- Capped at 40 particles (cosmetic ambient effect)

### 🎥 Smooth Camera
- Camera position/zoom eases toward a target using linear interpolation

### Summary
**It's a headless force-directed graph physics engine with decorative particles and a smooth camera, running at ~60 FPS.** There's no rendering code here — this is purely the simulation layer (the drawing would happen elsewhere reading the node/particle positions).
